definition: to scale (a height)/to ascend/to mount/to publish or record/to enter (e.g. in a register)/to press down with the foot/to step or tread on/to put on (shoes or trousers) (dialect)/to be gathered and taken to the threshing ground (old)

sentences.english: This will be the workhorse of China's lunar programme.
sentences.chinese: 這是中國登月項目中的“老黃牛”。

sentences.english: U. S shouldn't think other counties cannot go tothe moon because of the lack of technology.
sentences.chinese: 美國不應該認爲其他國家因爲缺乏技術沒能力登月。

sentences.english: US lunar pull-out leaves China shooting for moon.
sentences.chinese: 美國退出登月計劃讓中國瞄上月球。
我們都知道飛船登月的故事。

sentences.english: Never mind the two-party U.S.-Soviet moon race of old.
sentences.chinese: 忘記以前登月競賽的美蘇爭霸吧。

sentences.english: Apollo 11's lunar module onto the Sea of Tranquillity, and promptly fluffed his lines.
sentences.chinese: 號的登月艙，到達靜海，並迅速抖開繩索。

sentences.english: Why didn't the Lunar module show a flame when it took off from the Moon?
sentences.chinese: 爲什麼登月車從月球上面起飛的時候沒有火花？

sentences.english: The dark halo around the LM is from the astronauts' heavyfoot traffic.
sentences.chinese: 登月艙四周的黑色光環是宇航員負留下的深深腳印。

sentences.english: [picture of self pointing to man on moon] In the Apollo project of cooperation possible?
sentences.chinese: 一個類似於阿波羅登月那樣的合作項目是否有可能？

sentences.english: Mission officials at the Launch Control Centre following the successful launch.
sentences.chinese: 發射成功後位於發射控制中心內的登月任務官員。

sentences.english: Man's first landing on the moon was a feat of great daring.
sentences.chinese: 人類首次登月是一個勇敢的壯舉。

sentences.english: Anyway, how does sending a rocket to the moon help the peasants of Gansu?
sentences.chinese: 退一步講，登月計劃如何能幫助甘肅的農民脫貧？

sentences.english: Plans were big, first the moon, then Mars.
sentences.chinese: 規模宏大的計劃，首先登月，然後是火星。

sentences.english: Artificial intelligence turned out to be more like cancer research than a moon shot.
sentences.chinese: 人工智能相比於一次性的登月發射更類似於癌症研究。

sentences.english: Did the United States fake the moon landings?
sentences.chinese: 美國是否假造了登月事件？

sentences.english: It was published in all the newspapers.
sentences.chinese: 登月的新聞被刊載在所有的報紙上。

definition: moon landing/to land on the moon
the Apollo project (1961-1975), the NASA moon landing project
US National Aeronautics and Space Administration/NASA
NASA, National Aeronautics and Space Administration, agency of US government
